---
description: Use EXPLAIN via MCP query tool to validate SQL before applying it
globs: "**/*.sql"
alwaysApply: false
---

When editing a SQL file, validate non-trivial queries using the `postgres-readonly` MCP server before finalizing:

```
tool: query
sql: EXPLAIN <your query here>
```

`EXPLAIN` runs read-only and will catch syntax errors, missing tables, and invalid column references without executing the query. Use it when:
- Writing a new SELECT or WITH query
- Modifying a WHERE clause or JOIN condition
- Referencing columns you have not yet confirmed via `schema://table/{table_name}`
